headline: JPM's Feroli Sees 2 Rate Cuts, Solid 3Q Productivity
summary: Mike Feroli, JPMorgan chief U.S. economist, says slower job growth alongside steady GDP growth points to strong productivity gains. He notes signs of improvement in the second quarter and expects solid growth in the third. Feroli speaks with Romaine Bostick and Matt Miller on "The Close."
